== Description ==

This macro creates geodesic dome structures, which are spherical structures based on a network of great circles (geodesics) subdividing an icosahedron. Geodesic domes are used in architecture, engineering, and design for their structural efficiency and aesthetic appeal.

The macro provides a dialog for specifying dome parameters and generates a parametric object that can be modified after creation.

== How To Use ==

# Copy the macro file {{FileName|GeodesicDome.FCMacro}} and the {{FileName|geodesic_dome/}} folder to your FreeCAD Macro directory.
# Run the macro from {{MenuCommand|Macro → Macros... → GeodesicDome}}.
# A dialog will appear where you can set the dome parameters.
# Click OK to create the geodesic dome in your active document.

== Technical Details ==

* The macro is structured as a module ({{FileName|geodesic_dome/geodesic_dome.py}}) that can be imported independently, supporting save-restore of parametric objects.
* When run as a macro, it loads the module and shows the configuration dialog via {{incode|showDialog()}}.
* The dome geometry is derived from an icosahedron with frequency-based subdivision.
* The parametric object survives save-reload cycles because the macro registers itself as a FreeCAD feature Python object.

